```

That objectвҖҷs **identity never changes**.

***

# 3пёҸвғЈ Why `useRef` Breaks the Closure Problem

### The key difference

| State variable            | Ref                           |
| ------------------------- | ----------------------------- |
| Recreated on every render | Same object forever           |
| Captured by closures      | Object reference stays valid  |
| Snapshot in time          | Always points to latest value |

***

## The Core Insight (This is the вҖңahaвҖқ)

> вң… Closures capture the **ref object**, not the **value inside it**.

